Issue Identification:
- Identify the file or folder location (SharePoint, network drive, OneDrive)
- Determine the specific access issue (can't access, permission denied, missing)
- Verify the user's current access level
- Check if issue affects one user or multiple users

{% if issue_type == 'permission_denied' %}
Permission Request:
- Verify user has legitimate need for access
- Identify the data owner or manager
- Obtain approval for access change
- Add user to appropriate security group
- Set correct permission level (read, contribute, full control)
- Test access with user
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'missing_files' %}
Missing Files Investigation:
- Check recycle bin (local and SharePoint/OneDrive)
- Review version history for accidental changes
- Check if file was moved to different location
- Search for file by name across locations
- Review audit logs for delete/move actions
- Check sync conflicts folder if using OneDrive
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'sharepoint' %}
SharePoint Troubleshooting:
- Verify user can access SharePoint site
- Check site permissions and group membership
- Clear browser cache and try again
- Test with different browser
- Check for sync issues if using OneDrive sync
- Verify SharePoint service status
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'network_drive' %}
Network Drive Issues:
- Verify drive mapping is correct
- Check network connectivity to file server
- Verify user's AD group memberships
- Test accessing share via UNC path directly
- Check file server availability
- Review NTFS and share permissions
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'sync_issues' %}
OneDrive/Sync Issues:
- Check OneDrive sync status icon
- Review files pending sync
- Pause and resume sync
- Check for sync conflicts
- Verify available local disk space
- Reset OneDrive sync if needed
{% endif %}

Resolution:
- Confirm user can access required files
- Document permissions changed
- Notify data owner of access granted
- Update access documentation
- Schedule access review if temporary
